President Biden has announced six new nominees for U.S. Attorneys across the country. These individuals were chosen for their commitment to enforcing the law, professionalism, experience, dedication to equal justice, and commitment to the independence of the Department of Justice. The President has made addressing the increase in gun crime a priority, and confirming U.S. Attorneys is crucial for these efforts. The President has now announced a total of 43 nominees for U.S. Attorneys. The article provides brief biographies of each nominee.